30/01/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Commander Yves de Kermabon said on Thursday (January 29th) that the EULEX mission will be fully operational before spring. 
"We are in the middle of full deployment. 
There is much to be done, and the full deployment will be achieved by the end of the winter," de Kermabon said during his first visit to Gjakova, in western Kosovo.
In other news, Czech Foreign Minister Karel Schwarzenberg, whose country currently holds the EU's rotating presidency, said on Thursday that conditions must be created for EULEX to function. 
"We are working on the improvement of relations between Serbia and EULEX and on the normalisation of relations between Belgrade and Pristina," Schwarzenberg said. 
"The Balkans must be integrated in the EU," he added. 
(Telegrafi, Koha Ditore, Zeri, Express, Kohavision - 30/01/09)
